# Datasets

This project uses two real-world datasets.

---

## Part A — UK Road Accident Data (STATS19)

**File:** `accident_data_v1.0.0_2023.db`

This is an SQLite database provided by the UK Department for Transport containing STATS19 road accident records.

🔗 [UK DfT Road Safety Data](https://www.data.gov.uk/dataset/cb7ae6f0-4be6-4935-9277-47e5ce24a11f/road-safety-data)

The database contains three tables used in this project:
- `accident` — accident-level records (location, severity, time, conditions)
- `vehicle` — vehicle-level records (type, manoeuvre)
- `casualty` — casualty-level records (class, age, severity)

Place the file as:
```
data/
└── accident_data_v1.0.0_2023.db
```

---

## Part B — Facebook Social Network (SNAP)

**File:** `facebook_combined.txt`

An undirected edge list from Facebook ego-networks, compiled by the Stanford Network Analysis Platform (SNAP).

🔗 [Stanford SNAP — Facebook Dataset](https://snap.stanford.edu/data/ego-Facebook.html)

Place the file as:
```
data/
└── facebook_combined.txt
```

**Format:** Each line contains two space-separated node IDs representing an edge.
```
0 1
0 2
0 3
...
```
